abstract: The Fox show again grabs the 18-to-49 set.
snippet: The Fox show again grabs the 18-to-49 set.
lead_paragraph: It appears that Fox is content to fill the holes in its broadcast schedule with episodes of "The X Factor" and, so far, the strategy seems to be working. Simon Cowell and Co. once again led the network to an overall victory in the 18-to-49-year-old demographic and against Tuesday competition, "The X Factor" posted better 18-to-49 ratings than its previous Sunday and Thursday installments while drawing an average of 10.1 million total viewers.

headline.main: If It's Tuesday (or Sunday or Thursday), It Must Be 'X Factor'
